ng home setting."Generally, (when) you're talking nursing home and assisted living (facilities), they are confined environments, so people generally spend time closer together than they would have done in their own home. So that's, I think, one of the reasons there are higher risks of getting (an) infection in that environment," Wiberg said.Wiberg is also taking some precautions, including cutting his outpatient visits by about 85%, and he's relying more on telemedicine.             PARKVILLE, Md.
