rch 22.Towson University's main campus will be open even if in-person classes are restricted after spring break.But right now, the plans are to come back as normal after spring break, but that could change should things get worse.Towson University has suspended the remainder of the athletics varsity spring season, effective immediately. Teams suspending competition are men’s/women’s lacrosse,       baseball, softball, men’s/women’s golf, outdoor track & field and tennis.Towson announced the suspension of all spring break and summer 2020 study abroad programs.Loyola UniversityStarting Wednesday, March 11, in-person classes will be suspended at the university. Existing online courses will continue uninterrupted.Residents halls will close Friday the 13th at noon and students are expected to return home as soon as possible. Those who cannot return home must request permission to stay on campus.Starting March 18, classes will be taught online or electronically.In-person classes are expected to resume on April 1.Large-scale events with more than 50 people have been canceled through April 1. Outdoor athletic events will continue with restrictions to the number of allowed attendees.Maryland Day events scheduled for March 20 and Accepted Students Open House scheduled for March 14 will be postponed.Non-essential, university-affiliated travel is restricted until      further notice. The vice president in each area will determine whether      travel is essential.On Tuesday, university officials said 14 students are being self-quarantined after potential contact with a person may have tested positive with coronavirus.Officials said the students attended an event over spring break where they may have been in contact with the infected individual. The students were told not to return to campus until the quarantined period is over. They will go to the Campus Health Center and be checked out to make sure they are asymptomatic before they can return to class, officials said.Notre Dame