emic, that's the hard part."I send my love to them, always, but it's just always been hard. But they know this is where I need to be to achieve my dreams, and I've always appreciated them for that," Olivia Gruver said.WBAL-TV 11 News interviewed Olivia Gruver before the news came out that the Olympics would be postponed. After the news broke, in a text message, Olivia Gruver said, "It hurts a bit, but it's the right thing to do." Now, she can eat some ice cream.             REISTERSTOWN, Md.
