e had a certain personality. Also had a way with him where he had a certain charm and elegance," Clark said.His van advertised his fearlessness, bragging he could go anywhere to play anyone who wants to play."He said he would play all the men that were his age and he would beat them," said golfer Vernon Bailey. "When you saw him play, you would think, if he can do it, I can do it."Logan passed away in 2017 at the age of 97. He drove and played golf up until the end. Brooks said her father always wanted his story told."He wanted to continue when segregation was over to show that a black man is not limited to anything. He can do anything he wants to do, but all he has to do is have that dream," Brooks said.​             BALTIMORE
